* ============================================================
* METADATA_CONTINUATION_SMOKE_v2.dts
*
* Purpose:
*   Safe smoke test for DotScript apostrophe continuation and
*   x64 memo/catalog mechanics.
*
* Critical workflow rule:
*   This script DOES NOT set paths.
*   Run the environment script first:
*
*       DO metadata
*       DO metadata_continuation_smoke_v2
*
* Correction from v1:
*   Use APPEND, not APPEND BLANK.
*
* Safety:
*   Uses only META_CONT_SMOKE. Does not touch SYSTEM_* tables.
* ============================================================

SET ECHO OFF
ECHO ===== METADATA CONTINUATION SMOKE V2 START =====

* Show current paths for verification. Do not mutate them here.
SETPATH

* Clean only the smoke table/index in the already-selected metadata lane.
ERASE META_CONT_SMOKE
ERASE META_CONT_SMOKE.CDX

CREATE X64 META_CONT_SMOKE ( '
    SMOKE_ID C(32), '
    CANONICAL_NAME C(80), '
    IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS C(24), '
    OWNER_SUBSYSTEM C(48), '
    ACTIVE L, '
    NOTES M '
)

USE META_CONT_SMOKE
STRUCT

APPEND
REPLACE SMOKE_ID WITH "SMOKE_001"
REPLACE CANONICAL_NAME WITH "DotScript continuation"
REPLACE IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS WITH "implemented"
REPLACE OWNER_SUBSYSTEM WITH "dotscript"
REPLACE ACTIVE WITH .T.
REPLACE NOTES WITH "This row proves apostrophe line continuation, x64 long field metadata, memo write, and readback in the metadata lane."

LIST ALL
DISPLAY

CDX CREATE
CDX ADDTAG SMOKE_ID
CDX ADDTAG CANONICAL_NAME
CDX ADDTAG IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS
CDX ADDTAG OWNER_SUBSYSTEM
BUILDLMDB CLEAN YES

ECHO ===== POST-INDEX READBACK =====
USE META_CONT_SMOKE
SET INDEX TO META_CONT_SMOKE
SET ORDER TO TAG SMOKE_ID
LIST ALL
DISPLAY

ECHO ===== METADATA CONTINUATION SMOKE V2 END =====
